1. What is Salesforce Platform?

The Salesforce Platform is basically a place where you can 
build entire business applications — without needing to write 
code for everything. It runs on the cloud, so nothing is 
installed on your computer..

2)What is an App?

a collection of objects,tools,tabs that are grouped together for business purpose

object - it is place where we can store specific type of information like a table

tab - these are present at the top of the website ,it is cilckable button that opens an object

3)configuration -  use when the requirement is standard, straightforward, and salesforce already has a tool for it.
  code - use when the requirement is complex, involves custom logic, conditions across multiple objects

